    "body": "> `lighthouse vc` is still required, and its configuration can remain mostly the same. The only change necessary to the VC is the addition of the `--suggested-fee-recipient`. That's bullet point 2 here: https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/merge-migration.html#necessary-configuration\r\n\r\n@michaelsproul how should I use `--suggested-fee-recipient` arg? does it take a value? looks in code like it does, should that value be in quotation marks? or not? start with leading \"0x\"? I have not found any documentation about an **example usage** of this arg, that would be very helpful!\r\n\r\nTake a look at https://lighthouse-book.sigmaprime.io/suggested-fee-recipient.html \r\n\r\nI would like to see a change from current:\r\n\r\n```\r\nAssuming trustworthy nodes, the priority for the three methods is:\r\n\r\nvalidator_definitions.yml\r\n--suggested-fee-recipient provided to the VC.\r\n--suggested-fee-recipient provided to the BN.\r\n```\r\n\r\nto \r\n\r\n```\r\nAssuming trustworthy nodes, the priority for the three methods is:\r\n\r\nvalidator_definitions.yml\r\n`--suggested-fee-recipient \"<PLAIN_OLD_ETH_ADDRESS>\"` provided to the VC.\r\n`--suggested-fee-recipient \"<PLAIN_OLD_ETH_ADDRESS>\"` provided to the BN.\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd analogoulsy for section 2 and 3:\r\n\r\nChange from:\r\n```\r\nThe --suggested-fee-recipient can be provided to the VC to act as a default value for all validators where a suggested_fee_recipient is not loaded from another method.\r\n```\r\n\r\nto\r\n\r\n```\r\nThe `--suggested-fee-recipient \"<PLAIN_OLD_ETH_ADDRESS>\"` can be provided to the VC to act as a default value for all validators where a suggested_fee_recipient is not loaded from another method.\r\n```\r\n\r\nOr without quotation marks if that is the case...?",
